#
# Hardcoded SwiftUI `Text("Foo")` literal count — Humble UI G3 ratchet.
#
# Per ADR-021/043 + ADR-038, every user-visible string lives in
# `locales/*.json` and is read via `LocalizationService.shared.t("foo.key")`.
# A `Text("Foo")` literal bypasses i18n.
#
# Scope: top-level + nested .swift files under `Vauchi/Views/`.
# Scanned by `just lint ios` via `scripts/scripts/check-text-literal-count.sh`.
# Each retirement / localisation MR shrinks this number — the script fails
# CI if the count rises above the baseline.
#
# Audit log:
#   - 2026-05-02 audit baseline: 92 (cross-platform Humble-UI audit)
#   - After Phase 0  (retire dead views): 29
#   - After Phase 1a (7 retirements):     17
#   - After Phase 1b (BleExchange):       17
#   - After Phase 1c (LockScreen i18n):   15
#   - After Phase 1d (RestoreIdentity):   13  ← current baseline

13
